{"questionId":"6969","questionHtml":"<p>The only significant uncertainty is in the temperature measurement.</p>\n<p>Determine the absolute uncertainty in the calculated value of Δ<em>H</em> if the uncertainty in the temperature rise was ±0.2 °C.</p>","markschemeHtml":"<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 1:</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.2\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}} \\times \\frac{{100}}{{7.5\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}}}} = \">\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.5</mn>\n      <msup>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mo>∘</mo>\n      </msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong> 3 %/0.03&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>0.03 × 160 kJ<strong>»</strong> =&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>±<strong>»</strong> 5 <strong>«</strong>kJ<strong>»&nbsp;</strong>✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>ALTERNATIVE 2:</strong></em></p>\n<p><strong>«</strong><span class=\"mjpage\"><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"0.2\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}} \\times \\frac{{100}}{{7.5\\,^\\circ {\\text{C}}}} = \">\n  <mn>0.2</mn>\n  <msup>\n    <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n    <mo>∘</mo>\n  </msup>\n  <mrow>\n    <mtext>C</mtext>\n  </mrow>\n  <mo>×</mo>\n  <mfrac>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>100</mn>\n    </mrow>\n    <mrow>\n      <mn>7.5</mn>\n      <msup>\n        <mspace width=\"thinmathspace\"></mspace>\n        <mo>∘</mo>\n      </msup>\n      <mrow>\n        <mtext>C</mtext>\n      </mrow>\n    </mrow>\n  </mfrac>\n  <mo>=</mo>\n</math></span><strong>»</strong>&nbsp;3 %/0.03&nbsp;✔</p>\n<p><strong>«</strong>0.03&nbsp;× 180 kJ<strong>»</strong>&nbsp;=&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>±<strong>»</strong>&nbsp;5&nbsp;<strong>«</strong>kJ<strong>»&nbsp;</strong>✔</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em>Accept values in the range 4.1–5.5 «kJ».</em></p>\n<p><em>Award <strong>[2]</strong> for correct final answer.</em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>","meta":{"questionId":"6969","referenceCode":"18N.2.sl.TZ0.1b.iii","subjectId":"45-dp-chemistry-last-assessment-2024","title":"The only significant uncertainty is in the temperature measurement. Determine the absolute uncertainty in the calculated value of ΔH if the uncertainty in the temperature rise was ","paper":"2","level":"sl","questionNumber":"b.iii","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Core","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing","11.1 Uncertainties and errors in measurement and results","Core","Topic 11: Measurement and data processing"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}}}